## Decisions Made
- Use per-run unique temp files ($$.$RANDOM) with trap EXIT cleanup instead of fixed /tmp paths: Ensures concurrent agent safety and automatic cleanup on any exit path
- Use HEAD instead of capturing SHA via $(git log ...): After git commit, HEAD already points to the new commit — no variable capture needed
- Simplify record-decision to single-line -m flag: The decision: slug message is always single-line, so heredoc + command substitution was unnecessary overhead
- Simplify notes push failure report to omit reason: The stderr is already visible in Bash output; capturing it into a variable would require command substitution

## Problems Encountered
- Claude Code security layer blocks $(...) command substitution in Bash tool calls: Resolved by replacing all command substitution with temp files, -F flags, and sequential Bash calls

## Constraints Identified
- Claude Code Bash tool rejects any command containing $(...) or backtick substitution patterns: All skill templates that generate Bash commands must avoid these patterns entirely

