## Context
Session focused on eliminating command substitution patterns from three skill Bash templates (memento-commit, record-decision, bumping-version) that were being blocked by Claude Code's built-in security checks. Each skill was rewritten to use temp files with heredocs and -F flags, verified with end-to-end tests in a throwaway git repo. All three skills now produce identical git results without triggering security prompts.

